# AI Workspace Rules

## Memory safety

- Always search the workspace using semantic search before opening files.
- Only open files that are directly relevant to the current task.
- Never load the entire repository unless explicitly required.

## Efficiency

- Work with small file sets.
- Avoid scanning large directories unless necessary.
- Limit exploration to files directly connected to the problem.

## Repository safety

- Ignore dependency folders, build outputs, logs, and generated assets.

## Editing strategy

- Prefer minimal targeted edits.
- Avoid large refactors unless explicitly requested.
- Open at most a few files per reasoning step.
